IPS Web – XSS Filter Validation Test Instructions

Purpose

The application now includes a security filter that validates query parameters to protect against Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks and malformed requests.

These tests confirm that:
	1.	Normal requests continue to work
	2.	Malicious inputs are blocked
	3.	An appropriate error page is shown instead of a server error
	4.	Long query values are rejected

Testing should be performed in DEV or CAT environment only.

⸻

Test Environment

Use the IPS Web application URL in CAT/DEV:

Example:

https://<env-host>/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml


⸻

Test Case 1 – Normal Application Flow (Baseline)

Steps
	1.	Open the IPS Web application.
	2.	Navigate through the normal user flow (enter phone/email etc).
	3.	Submit the form.

Expected Result
	•	Page loads normally
	•	No errors occur
	•	Normal workflow continues

This confirms that the new filter does not affect valid requests.

⸻

Test Case 2 – Script Injection Attempt

Test URL

Append the following query parameter to the page URL:

?test=<script>

Encoded version (preferred):

?test=%3Cscript%3E

Example

https://<env-host>/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml?test=%3Cscript%3E

Expected Result

The request should be blocked.

User should see a friendly error page similar to:

We couldn’t complete your request.
For security reasons, the page you requested contained characters that are not allowed.

The application should NOT display a server stack trace or HTTP 500 page.

⸻

Test Case 3 – JavaScript Keyword Injection

Test URL

?cmd=alert(1)

Example:

https://<env-host>/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml?cmd=alert(1)

Expected Result

The request should be blocked and show the security error page.

⸻

Test Case 4 – Event Handler Injection

Test URL

?param=onerror=alert(1)

Expected Result

Request should be blocked and display the security error page.

⸻

Test Case 5 – Valid Parameter (Should Pass)

Test URL

?do=start

Example:

https://<env-host>/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml?do=start

Expected Result
	•	Page loads normally
	•	No error page appears

This confirms valid parameters are allowed.

⸻

Test Case 6 – Valid URL Parameter

Test URL

?appURL=https://devpx-custreg.usps.com/entreg/secure/IdentityConfirmAction_input

Expected Result
	•	Request should NOT be blocked
	•	Page loads normally

This confirms legitimate URLs are allowed.

⸻

Test Case 7 – Oversized Parameter Test

The application blocks query parameters larger than 2048 characters.

Steps
	1.	Open browser DevTools console
	2.	Run the following script:

var base = window.location.origin + "/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml";
var large = "a".repeat(2050);
window.open(base + "?test=" + large);

Expected Result

The request should be blocked and display the security error page.

⸻

Expected Behavior Summary

Scenario	Expected Result
Normal application usage	Works normally
Script injection (<script>)	Blocked
JavaScript execution (alert(1))	Blocked
Event handler (onerror)	Blocked
Valid parameter (do=start)	Allowed
Valid URL parameter	Allowed
Query parameter > 2048 chars	Blocked


